-- World Bank, ADB Express Concern Over Ivory Coast's Status After Elections
-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 2010-12-06T01:40:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-06/world-bank-adb-express-concern-over-ivory-coast-s-status-after-elections.html
The World Bank Group and the African
Development Bank “view with great concern and frustration” the
uncertainty following the Ivory Coast elections, and will
“reassess the usefulness and effectiveness” of their programs
in light of the “breakdown in governance,” the two
organizations said in an e-mailed joint statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Simpson at 
 jsimpson12@bloomberg.net  